+## CVE-2025-8941 — False Positive for `pam` 1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6 (Ubuntu Jammy)
+
+## Overview: What Is CVE-2025-8941?
+
+CVE-2025-8941 is a privilege escalation vulnerability in the `pam_namespace` module of
+`linux-pam`. The module used path-based operations vulnerable to symlink attacks and
+time-of-check-time-of-use (TOCTOU) race conditions, allowing a local user to escalate
+privileges to root.
+
+**CVSS Score:** 7.8 HIGH (CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)
+**CWE:** CWE-22 – Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory
+**CNA:** Red Hat, Inc. (published 2025-08-13)
+
+---
+
+## 📌 CVE-2025-8941 – False Positive for pam:1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6 (Ubuntu Jammy)
+
+**Component:** `libpam-modules` in Ubuntu Jammy 22.04 LTS
+**Affected version reported:** 1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6
+**Verdict:** FALSE POSITIVE — the vulnerability is already fully remediated.
+
+---
+
+## 🔍 CVE Relationship: CVE-2025-8941 vs CVE-2025-6020
+
+CVE-2025-8941 is explicitly described in NVD as:
+> *"This CVE provides a 'complete' fix for CVE-2025-6020."*
+
+And in CVE.org (cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2025-8941) with the title:
+> *"Linux-pam: incomplete fix for cve-2025-6020"*
+
+This means CVE-2025-8941 was raised to complete **Red Hat's** incomplete fix for
+CVE-2025-6020. Ubuntu's fix for CVE-2025-6020 was already comprehensive and complete.
+
+| CVE | Published | Ubuntu fix shipped | Completeness |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| CVE-2025-6020 | 2025-06-17 | 1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6 (2025-06-18) | Complete (3 patches) |
+| CVE-2025-8941 | 2025-08-13 | Not needed — already covered | N/A for Ubuntu |
+
+**Ubuntu is NOT listed as an affected platform in CVE-2025-8941's product status.**
+Only Red Hat products are listed as affected.
+
+---
+
+## ✅ pam:1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6 — Why This is a False Positive
+
+Ubuntu Jammy shipped version 1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6 on 2025-06-18 with three patches
+for CVE-2025-6020:
+
+- `debian/patches-applied/CVE-2025-6020-1.patch` — Converts all path-based
+  operations in pam_namespace to file-descriptor-based operations (introduces
+  `secure_opendir()` replacing `protect_dir()`).
+- `debian/patches-applied/CVE-2025-6020-2.patch` — Adds `check_safe_path()`
+  function and passes safety flags ($5, $6) to namespace.init.
+- `debian/patches-applied/CVE-2025-6020-3.patch` — Hardens ownership checks
+  by removing the root-group exception in `secure_opendir()`.
+
+These three patches together implement every security change that CVE-2025-8941
+requires, including those that Red Hat's equivalent fix omitted.
+
+---
+
+## 🔬 Binary Proof — Tested on Official Package
+
+The compiled binary `/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/security/pam_namespace.so`
+from the official `libpam-modules=1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6` package was inspected.
+
+**Vulnerable code strings — ABSENT (0 occurrences):**
+- `"Error creating or accessing instance parent"` — old path-based check_inst_parent
+- Path-string arguments to `umount()` — replaced by fd-based `umount2()`
+
+**Secure replacement strings — PRESENT:**
+- `/proc/self/fd/%d` — magic link fd-based operations (2 occurrences)
+- `/proc/self/fd/%d/%s` — race-free mkdtemp via fd
+- `"Error accessing instance parent, %m"` — new fd-based (no path variable)
+- `"Error getting fd to %s"` — secure_getfilecon present
+- `"Error mounting %s on %s (%s on %s), %m"` — fd-based bind mount present
+- `"polyptr->instance_parent %s access error"` — new struct field present
+- `umount2` — lazy fd-based unmount in use
+
+**check_safe_path() active — 3 distinct error messages PRESENT:**
+- `"Path deemed unsafe: Symlink %s should be owned by root"`
+- `"Path deemed unsafe: %s is expected to be a directory"`
+- `"Path deemed unsafe: %s should be owned by root, and not be writable by group or others"`
+
+**namespace.init safety flags $5 and $6 — PRESENT** in the installed script.
+
+---
+
+## ⚠️ Why No Fix Is Needed
+
+- Ubuntu Jammy 1.4.0-11ubuntu2.6 already includes **all** security improvements
+  mandated by CVE-2025-8941 via its comprehensive CVE-2025-6020 patch series.
+- The CVE-2025-8941 patch, when applied to the Ubuntu source after CVE-2025-6020,
+  produces "Reversed (previously applied) patch detected" for pam_namespace.h and
+  namespace.init, and fails 33 out of 34 hunks in pam_namespace.c — confirming
+  the changes are already present.
+- Vulnerability scanners reporting CVE-2025-8941 on this version are generating
+  **false positives** due to CVE aliasing between the Red Hat and Ubuntu fixes.
+
